A 40-YEAR-OLD man is seriously ill in hospital in Glasgow after he was struck by a car in Biggar.The man suffered head injuries after he was hit by a Ford Kuga while crossing the A73 at Sherifflats Road, Thankerton, at 11.10am yesterday.He was taken by helicopter to the South Glasgow University Hospital where he is said to be in a serious condition.The 71-year-old driver was not injured.Police are appealing for witnesses to contact Motherwell police on 101.